<author><name><![CDATA[dXtr]]></name></author>
<updated>2005-09-06T10:26:45-07:00</updated>
<published>2005-09-06T10:26:45-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=531&amp;p=4307#p4307</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=531&amp;p=4307#p4307"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[dsp instruction?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=531&amp;p=4307#p4307"><![CDATA[
the DSP instruction isn't really a instruction as I discoverd but a command for the MSS engine.. he had added a special instruction that his engine translated in to real code.. example:<br /><br />he sends to the APU through the I/O ports on the SNES<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">DSP $00, $3F</div><br /><br />and that got translated to something like:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">$06, $00, $3F</div><br /><br />that was put into the different I/O ports and transferd to the APU where his engine would use it like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">SCPU:<br />...<br />mov IOport0, #$06<br />mov IOport1, #$00<br />mov IOport2, #$3F<br />...<br /><br />----------------------<br />APU:<br />...<br />cmp IOport0, #$06<br />beq SetDSP<br />...<br /><br />SetDSP:<br />mov $F2, IOport1<br />mov $F3, IOport2<br />ret<br /></div><br /><br />and about the other commands.. sorry havn't read up on those<br /><br />edit:<br />that's just one way it's used.. the other one is that he tells the engine to jump to that specific code on the apu to for example init the apu.<br /><br />sorry if I'm not good at explaining.. it's much easier to understand if you watch his code...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=15">dXtr</a> — Tue Sep 06, 2005 10:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
